    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "`SecureRandom` can definitely block on lack of entropy even on the most recent JDKs but that is because it reads from `/dev/random` when creating its initial seed.  But as long as we are reusing a single instance of `SecureRandom` it shouldn't block and fortunately `SecureRandom` is thread safe, unlike the plain `Random`.",
